article.headline: Texas St. 102, Texas-Pan American 75
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- Jonathan Sloan scored 20 points to lead Texas State to a 102-75 win over Texas-Pan American on Wednesday night. Sloan was nearly perfect, shooting 6 of 7 from the field and 8 of 9 from the free-throw line. Brent Benson scored 16, and Ty Gough added 14 for the Bobcats (4-1). Corey Jefferson and Brandon Bush each had 13 points, while Ryan White added 10. Emmanuel Jones scored 17 and Brian Burrell added 16 for Texas-Pan American (3-1). Zach Trader had 11 points, and Paul Stoll scored 10. Texas State manhandled the Broncs on the boards, posting a 56-28 rebounding advantage. The Broncs also had a rough night shooting, hitting 34 percent from the field -- 18 percent from beyond the 3-point arc.
